  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The COVID-19 Open Research Dataset (CORD-19), hosted on Zenodo, serves as a vital resource for the scientific community, accruing 2,909 views and 2,771 downloads, underscoring its significant engagement and utility in pandemic research.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The COVID-19 Open Research Dataset (CORD-19), created by a team including authors from the Allen Institute and hosted on Zenodo, stands as a foundational dataset in the exploration of COVID-19 research. Garnering 2,909 views and 2,771 downloads, it demonstrates a substantial commitment to data accessibility and community engagement in the urgent field of pandemic response.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Despite the absence of funding support, the dataset's credibility is implied through its association with credible institutions, particularly the Allen Institute. The dataset has been cited four times, showcasing its relevance to current research efforts, and it is gaining traction particularly in venues such as bioRxiv and the Journal of Medical Internet Research, where it has been leveraged in both preprint and review contexts.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The lack of external social media mentions or community discussions on platforms like Reddit highlights a focused academic engagement rather than widespread public discourse. However, the dataset's proven downstream reuse, indicated by four successful citations, illustrates its active utility in advancing scientific knowledge and enabling subsequent research contributions.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The dataset exemplifies a strong commitment to the principles of open science by sharing research outputs early and freely available to the community. As a significant resource for researchers confronting COVID-19 challenges, CORD-19 is pivotal in facilitating ongoing investigations into the pandemic, ensuring that the research community remains prepared and informed through data-driven insights.</p>",
